						<summary>

						<p>On the fourth pillar of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 25: 931-32 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription records the gift of 90 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to the deity Tirumaṟaikkāṭṭu-mahādēva, probably by Nakki, a female resident of Nandipuram(?).</p>						

						</summary>
